<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#871f78">Originally posted by Dumathoin on 11-04-2000 02:00 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I totally agree with Muse on this one. 

There should be dynamic content for ALL levels -- newbie mid-level or hi-level. 

As Muse quoted that statement, the Verant statement sounded "condescending" to lower levels by calling it a transitional stage. 

Another way to translate what they said:

"From now on, we will only add future and dynamic content for uber-level players. We won't bother adding dynamic content or even refresh the stale (and often tedious) content for newbie or mid-level players. They don't warrant further attention, since they are only a transitional stage. We only wish to reward exciting possibilities and surprises for those players who have wasted 1-2 years of their lives building up a 55+ level character. Thank you for understanding." 

Implications of this statement: 

#1. Twinking is perfectly good. Twinking is the easiest way to help you get out of the low level stages. Why bother any more time suffering in the low to mid level stages with horrible equipment? 

#2. E-bay accounts are perfectly OK. This is another good way to make sure that you will not have to go thru months of suffering thru those "transitional" newbie and mid-level stages. Why suffer months of tedious and stale dungeon crawl when you can purchase an uber-account from the start? 

#3. Mindless Power-leveling is all that matters. Dont bother socializing. Dont bother making friends, unless they are from an uber-guild. Don't even waste time in useless (non-profitable) trade skills like Brewing. They only get in the way of you reaching that magical level 50+. Also, don't bother getting any sleep. 

Is this the kind of Play Ethics that Verant wants us to buy into? I hope not. \
</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
